    longTailKeywords: ["government response to AI job displacement", "preparing workforce for AI disruption in India", "how AI affects education policy United States", "reskilling for AI economy UK", "AI curriculum development Australia"],
    featuredImagePrompt: "A conceptual, industry-specific visual depicting the complex intersection of AI, education, and the global workforce. The image should feature a dynamic, non-literal composition. On one side, abstract representations of learning (e.g., stylized open books, neural network patterns, data streams forming knowledge symbols). On the other side, conceptual elements of the workforce (e.g., diverse, anonymous human silhouettes in dynamic poses, gears, upward-trending graphs, digital interfaces). AI elements should bridge these two, perhaps as glowing circuits or abstract digital brains connecting the 'education' and 'workforce' sides. Use a sophisticated color palette of blues, greens, and subtle purples, conveying both innovation and the societal challenge. Avoid showing specific classrooms, offices, or identifiable faces. The visual should feel future-oriented, strategic, and globally resonant, highlighting the policy dimension. Focus on a high-level, impactful representation of systems interacting.",
