      tokenOverview: "Bitcoin (BTC) is the world\'s first and largest decentralized digital currency, operating on a peer-to-peer network without central authority. It serves primarily as a store of value and a medium of exchange, underpinning the broader cryptocurrency market.",
      tokenUtility: "BTC\'s primary utility is as a censorship-resistant digital store of value, often referred to as \'digital gold.\' It also functions as a medium of exchange for transactions and a base pair for trading other cryptocurrencies. Its fixed supply and halving events contribute to its scarcity and perceived value.",
      tokenomics: "Bitcoin has a hard cap of 21 million coins. New bitcoins are introduced through a process called \'mining,\' with the supply rate being halved approximately every four years (halving events). This predictable, disinflationary issuance schedule is a core aspect of its tokenomics.",
