      tokenUtility: "Bitcoin primarily serves as a store of value, a medium of exchange, and a hedge against inflation. Solana\'s SOL token is used for network transaction fees, staking to secure the network, and governance participation. It also acts as the base currency for various dApps within its ecosystem.",
      tokenomics: "Bitcoin has a hard cap of 21 million BTC, with its supply growth controlled by halving events every four years, making it deflationary. Solana has an inflationary supply with a decreasing inflation rate, incentivizing staking through rewards. Both have mechanisms to manage supply and demand.",
